The paper proposes a deep decision tree architecture for discriminative dictionary learning from adversarial multi-agent trajectories. This involves clustering and fine-tuning player role weights using backpropagation. The paper focuses on soccer tracking data, which suggests a strong likelihood of the paper belonging to the sub-categories of machine learning (cs.LG), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), computer vision (cs.CV), social and information networks (cs.SI), and game theory (cs.GT).
